The paper deals with online combinatorial optimization problems, which are typically studied in the computer science subfield of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of no-regret algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and online decision-making problems, suggesting a connection to the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also presents hardness results, indicating a connection to computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and game theory (cs.GT).
